A lone traveler sits on a sleek airport bench in a vast, empty terminal at night, surrounded by rows of darkened storefront shutters with their metal grates pulled down. Warm amber light from distant ceiling fixtures casts long shadows across polished floors that reflect like still water. A single vending machine glows neon blue in the distance, its light cutting through the quiet darkness. The scene captures the melancholy solitude of being stranded between destinations, with massive floor-to-ceiling windows revealing the black void of the tarmac outside. Style: cinematic photorealistic with moody noir lighting, emphasizing isolation and the strange beauty of empty commercial spaces after hours.
